title: Lygia Pape Tecelar (Weaving) Unmatted Print
description:
Unmatted print developed from Lygia Pape’s Tecelare (Weaving), 1954, from exhibit Lygia Pape: Tecelares at The Art Institute of Chicago.

Lygia Pape (1927–2004) was a key figure in the development of contemporary art in Brazil, dedicated to exploring new visual languages and multiple media, including painting, performance, printmaking, and sculpture.

  • Print Reproduction
  • Image size:  8.75 x 11 in.
  • Full poster size: 11 x 14 in.
  • Material: Premium Cardstock
